news.title: Amnesty scheme sought for property tax defaulters in Kolhapur
news.para: This demand has been raised against the backdrop of the KMC slapping pre-seizure notices to property owners against pending tax dues. The financial year will end next month and given the sluggish tax recovery, the civic body is pushing down harder on tax defaulters.

news.title: Skanska profits hold up, construction orders climb
news.para: The Nordic region's largest builder, and one of the biggest in the United States, reported on Friday operating earnings of 3.53 billion Swedish crowns ($339.8 million) in the quarter, down from 3.63 billion a year earlier.

news.title: Oberoi Realty acquires eight acres land in Thane for Rs 192.31 crore
news.para: This land purchased from Blue Star are adjoining the existing lands owned by Oberoi Realty admeasuring approximately 60 acres.

news.title: Coimbatore civic body continues stern action against wilful property tax defaulters
news.para: The civic body is pushing hard to cross 90% of the target by the end of the financial year, which is approaching fast. It had achieved 87% of the target at the end of the last financial year.

news.title: Kansai Nerolac Paints' net profit dip 13.05% in Q3 FY23
news.para: Kansai Nerolac Paints' consolidated total income stood at Rs 1,834.19 crore in Q3 FY23, a marginal growth of 0.76 per cent from Rs 1,820.31 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Over 500 villages of Ropar digitally updated
news.para: Swamitwa mission director Keshav Hingonia reviewed the progress of the scheme and said the aim of the scheme is to issue property cards to the owners of the houses in the red line areas in the state. So far, 536 villages have been verified in Ropar.

news.title: Star Cement's net profit up 20.65% in Q3 FY23
news.para: Star Cement's consolidated total income stood at Rs 631.27 crore in Q3 FY23, a growth of 12.34 per cent from Rs 561.93 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: FIR against 40 Ramgarh brick kiln owners
news.para: Mining inspector Binod Bihari Paramanik on Wednesday had submitted a written complaint on behalf of the district mining department to the Ramgarh police station against the erring 40 brick kiln owners.

news.title: Prism Johnson's net loss widens to Rs 63.35 crore in Q3 FY23
news.para: Prism Johnson's consolidated total income stood at Rs 1,785.94 crore in Q3 FY23, a growth of 8.41 per cent from Rs 1,647.42 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: NSE, BSE put Ambuja Cements, other Adani firms under short-term ASM
news.para: Apart from Adani Enterprises, the other two firms listed by the exchanges are -- Adani Ports and Special Economic Zone and Ambuja Cements.

news.title: GIC Housing Finance's net profit dips 14.46% in Q3 FY23
news.para: GIC Housing Finance's consolidated total income stood at Rs 284.29 crore in Q3 FY23, a dip of 2.97 per cent from Rs 292.98 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Redevelopment of Delhi's GPRA colonies held up in absence of tree transplantation nod: Govt
news.para: ​In a written reply to a question in Lok Sabha, Union Minister of State for Housing and Urban Affairs Kaushal Kishore said the Kasturba Nagar project will be executed in two phases.

news.title: Sourav Ganguly seeks Kolkata civic body's nod to demolish Lower Rawdon Street bungalow
news.para: The handover of the Rs 40-crore property had become a talk of the town after Ganguly expressed his desire to shift to his new prime central Kolkata address from his Behala residence.

news.title: Cement truck operators to submit proposal on freight rates to Himachal Pradesh government
news.para: ​Two cement plants at Barmana (Bilaspur district) and Darlaghat (Solan district) owned by ACC Limited and Ambuja Cements, respectively, have been closed due to a dispute over freight charges, and operators engaged in carriage of cement and clinkers are on the roads.

news.title: India Cements posts net profit of Rs 111 crore in Q3 FY23
news.para: India Cements' consolidated total income stood at Rs 1,292.26 crore in Q3 FY23, a growth of 10.63 per cent from Rs 1,168.12 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.
